    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A towering skeletal form, humanoid but distorted. Tattered robes of ancient cloth. Wrapped in chains of bone. Eyes are hollow voids glowing pale blue. Voice sounds like wind through a tomb — beautiful and terrifying. The Bone-Singer has absorbed so many corpses and so much undeath that it has become something more than a draugr, capable of raising the ancient dead at will.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Wail of the Dead</strong> (Main, Area 30ft, Presence): T1 3 psychic; T2 6 psychic + frightened EoNT; T3 9 psychic + frightened (save ends).</li><li><strong>Drain Life</strong> (Main, Ranged 20ft, Presence): T1 4 necrotic (Bone-Singer heals 4); T2 8 necrotic + heals 8; T3 12 necrotic + heals 12.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Arise, Arise:</strong> Triggered 1/round (Rounds 1-3): raise 1-2 Barrow-Draugr anywhere within 60 ft.</li><li><strong>Choir of Death:</strong> 1/combat when below 15 SP: all within 60 ft take 12 psychic + Presence test or stunned EoNT.</li><li><strong>Dread Aura:</strong> Living creatures within 10 ft: bane on Presence tests.</li><li><strong>Undead Nature:</strong> Immune to cold, poison, fear. Resist fire +3 (takes +3 from fire/radiant).</li></ul><p><strong>MALICE</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Requiem of the Dead (3M, below 28 SP):</strong> 12 psychic, 40 ft radius. Presence test or stunned EoNT.</li></ul><p>Beat 14, Bone-Fields. Raises Barrow-Draugr each round. Defeating it ends the encounter. ES 20.</p>",
